FT  04 MAR 93 / International Company News: Sumitomo Heavy cuts dividend and
forecast
SUMITOMO Heavy Industries, a leading Japanese shipbuilder, is to cut its
annual dividend by Y1 to Y3 per share for the year to March 1993 due to a
sharp fall in profits.
Sumitomo also announced a downward revision of its profits forecast. It now
expects non-consolidated pre-tax profits to fall to Y1.5bn (Dollars 12.7m),
down from an earlier estimate of Y3bn. Sales are now projected to total
Y295bn, down from a previous projection of Y300bn.
